children.text: The balustrade in this area has been constructed with a gap greater than the allowable 125mm.
Part 3.9.2.3 Balustrades or other Barrier Construction of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that

‘Openings in barriers (including decorative balustrades) must be constructed so that they do not permit a 125 mm sphere to pass through it and for stairways, the opening is measured above the nosing line of the stair treads (see Figure 3.9.2.3)’ .
This balustrade must be immediately rectified so that it is installed in accordance with the requirements of the BCA.
